questions.question: How much do local plumbers charge per hour?
questions.snippet: Most plumbers charge between $45 and $150 per hour. Residential plumbing jobs often fall on the lower end, while commercial or emergency repairs push rates higher. Additional fees may apply for travel, equipment, or after-hours services. Understanding these extras can prevent surprises.
questions.title: How Much Should a Plumber Charge Per Hour? - Right Solution Plumbing
